  "description": "Simple fabric mod that allows to take Villagers on a leash.",
  "body": "# Leash Villager\n<!-- SVG version -->\n<img alt=\"fabric\" height=\"56\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@intergrav/devins-badges@3/assets/cozy/supported/fabric_vector.svg\"> <!-- SVG version -->\n<img alt=\"forge\" height=\"56\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@intergrav/devins-badges@3/assets/cozy/unsupported/forge_vector.svg\"> <!-- SVG version -->\n<a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/leash-villager\" target=\"_blank\"  rel=\"noopener\"><img alt=\"curseforge\" height=\"56\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@intergrav/devins-badges@3/assets/cozy/available/curseforge_vector.svg\"></a>\n  \nVery simple mod that allows to leash Villagers, making it easier to transport them instead of using boats or the really slow happy ghast.  \n\n## 📖How to use\n1. Walk up to a Villager\n2. Right click on it while holding a lead\n3. You have now leashed a Villager!\n\n<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/RzFv8pLqlgs\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n\n## 🔗External links\n<a href=\"https://www.planetminecraft.com/member/nico4play/\" target=\"_blank\"  rel=\"noopener\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/PTAiKsV.png\" alt=\"PlanetMinecraft Link Button\" width=\"40\" /></a>\n<a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/members/nico4play/projects\" target=\"_blank\"  rel=\"noopener\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/B6lsNn0.png\" alt=\"CurseForge Link Button\" width=\"40\" /></a> ",
